1. What is React?
React is a JavaScript library used for building user interfaces, mainly for single-page applications.
Created by Facebook, it allows developers to build reusable UI components.

2. Setting Up React
Method 1: Using Create React App (CRA)
npx create-react-app my-app
cd my-app
npm start

Method 2: Using Vite (Faster & Modern)
npm create vite@latest my-app --template react
cd my-app
npm install
npm run dev

3. React Components
Components are the building blocks of a React app.

Types:
Function Components (Modern & recommended)

Class Components

3.1 Function Component Example
function Welcome() {
  return <h1>Hello React!</h1>;
}

export default Welcome;
3.2 Class Component Example
class Welcome extends React.Component {
  render() {
    return <h1>Hello React!</h1>;
  }
}


4. JSX (JavaScript XML)
JSX allows you to write HTML inside JavaScript.

Example:
const element = <h1>Welcome to React</h1>;
Rules of JSX:
Must return single parent element

Use className instead of class

Use {} to include JavaScript expressions

Example:

const name = "Purushoth";
return <h2>Hello {name}</h2>;


5. Props (Component Inputs)
Props are used to send data to components.

Example:
function Greeting(props) {
  return <h1>Hello {props.name}</h1>;
}

<Greeting name="Purushoth" />


6. State (Component Data)
State is data that changes over time.

Using useState Hook:
import { useState } from "react";

function Counter() {
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0);

  return (
    <>
      <h2>Count: {count}</h2>
      <button onClick={() => setCount(count + 1)}>Increase</button>
    </>
  );
}


7. Event Handling
React uses camelCase for events.

<button onClick={handleClick}>Click Me</button>

function handleClick() {
  alert("Button clicked!");
}


8. Conditional Rendering
Using if:
if (loggedIn) return <Dashboard />;
else return <Login />;
Using ternary:
{loggedIn ? <Dashboard /> : <Login />}


9. Lists & Keys
Example:
const items = ["Apple", "Orange", "Banana"];

return (
  <ul>
    {items.map((item, index) => (
      <li key={index}>{item}</li>
    ))}
  </ul>
);
Keys help React identify elements in a list.

10. useEffect Hook
Used for:
API calls
Timers
Subscriptions
Example:
import { useEffect } from "react";
useEffect(() => {
  console.log("Component mounted");
}, []);


